The intrinsic gain of a bipolar transistor, denoted as $A_{i}$, similar to MOS transistors, represents the highest achievable gain using that single transistor and is expressed by

$$
\begin{equation*}
A_{i}=g_{m} r_{o}=V_{A} / V_{T} \tag{8.44}
\end{equation*}
$$

Key Point: Active BJTs typically exhibit an intrinsic gain that exceeds that of MOS transistors and remains unaffected by the operating point.

